  "prompt": "What is infant mortality rate?",
  "response": "Infant mortality rate (IMR) is the number of deaths of infants under one year old per 1,000 live births. This rate is often used as an indicator of the overall health and well-being of a population, as well as the effectiveness of a country's healthcare system. Factors that can influence infant mortality rates include access to prenatal and postnatal care, socioeconomic status, and the prevalence of infectious diseases.",
